<TITLE> Taliban behead Afghan hostage: spokesman </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KANDAHAR, Afghanistan, June 5 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The Taliban beheaded on Tuesday one of the five Afghan hostages after the government failed to hand over the body of a slain commander for the militant group, a purported spokesman said. Shahabuddin Attal, who introduces himself as a Taliban spokesman, warned the guerrillas will chop off the heads of the other hostages should the government again fail to hand over the body of Mullah Dadullah, who US-led forces killed last month
